# Release archive hygiene — drop contributor/CI/dev artifacts from `git archive` output.
# Affects only `git archive` (release ZIPs/tarballs), not `git clone` or working tree.
# See docs/spec.md "v2.6.1 — Release Archive Hygiene" (REVISION 2) for KEEP/DROP rationale.
#
# IMPORTANT — `gitattributes(5)` does NOT honor negation (`!pattern`) — verified empirically
# 2026-05-11. `scripts/` still needs a surgical per-file DROP (see below). `docs/` uses a
# directory-prefix DROP (`docs/internal/`) instead — a real `export-ignore` directory match,
# not a negation — so a new `docs/*.md` file is public by default unless placed under
# `docs/internal/`; three Council-tooling paths are exempted individually (v2.8.0 ADR-037).

# --- Root files (DROP) ---
.gitignore              export-ignore
.markdownlint.jsonc     export-ignore
.markdownlintignore     export-ignore
CHANGELOG.md            export-ignore
CONTRIBUTING.md         export-ignore

# --- Directories (DROP entire subtree) ---
.github/                export-ignore
tests/                  export-ignore
upstream-contribution/  export-ignore

# --- Surgical DROP: scripts/ (KEEP setup-folders.sh and setup-folders.ps1; DROP install-pre-commit.sh) ---
scripts/install-pre-commit.sh   export-ignore

# --- docs/ (default-internal convention, v2.8.0 ADR-037 — a NEW docs/*.md ships to
# users ONLY if placed outside docs/internal/; inverts the prior per-file allowlist) ---
docs/internal/          export-ignore
# Council-tooling-exempt (stay at docs/ root, individually dropped — no path-override
# mechanism exists for these three; see docs/architecture.md ADR-037):
docs/spec.md            export-ignore
docs/retro.md           export-ignore
docs/patterns.md        export-ignore

# --- Meta (self-ignore) ---
.gitattributes          export-ignore
